#!/bin/sh
set -x

cd /home/schmidm/faststorage/ClaudiaI/Effie_RNAseq_bams

bam_file="07_Ars2-tot-3-rep_namesorted.bam" #..or other..#

echo "counting introns "
gtf="/home/schmidm/annotations/hg19/RefSeqGRCh37.3/ref_GRCh37.p5_top_level_introns.gtf"

htseq-count -f bam -s reverse -t intron -m intersection-strict \
${bam_file} $gtf > ${bam_file/.bam/.intron_strict_table_namesorted}

echo "done"

code not run only shown for documentation

path_to_RNAseq <- '/Users/schmidm/Documents/other_people_to_and_from/ClaudiaI/Effie_RNAseq_lists/Refseqv3_intron_counts'

regex_Claudia <- '-rep_namesorted.intron_strict_table_namesorted'

intron_files_Claudia <- dir(path_to_RNAseq) %>% keep(grepl(regex_Claudia, .))

introns_df_Claudia <- lapply(seq_along(intron_files_Claudia), function(i) { 
  read.table(paste(path_to_RNAseq, intron_files_Claudia[i], sep='/'),
                      colClasses = c('factor', 'integer'),
                      col.names = c('gene', 'counts')) %>%
    mutate(file = sub(regex_Claudia, '', intron_files_Claudia[i]) %>% 
                  sub('07_', '', .) %>% 
                  sub('-tot-', '_', .))
}) %>%
  bind_rows() %>%
  spread(file, counts) %>%
  tbl_df

run DESeq2 on intronic counts

create all info for the DESeq2 run

read_df <- mRNA_introns_df %>%
  unite(gene, c(gene_id, gene_name), sep=':') %>%
  remove_rownames %>%
  data.frame %>%
  column_to_rownames(var='gene')


coldata <- data.frame(condition = colnames(read_df) ) %>%
  tidyr::separate(condition, c('siRNA', 'replicate'), by='_', extra='drop') %>%
  mutate(condition = paste0(siRNA, '_intron'))

rownames(coldata) <- colnames(read_df)


ddsFullCountTable <- DESeqDataSetFromMatrix(
countData = read_df,
colData = coldata,
design = ~ condition)

we estimate sizefactors etc using one combined DESeq2 object, holding both Nicolas and Claudias data

dds <- DESeq(ddsFullCountTable)
save(dds, file='../data/RNAseq/RefSeqv3_intron_DESeq2.RData')

Differential expression

For differential expression each comparison is done separately

dds_ars_intron <- results(dds, contrast=c('condition', 'Ars2_intron', 'eGFP_intron'))
dds_z18_intron <- results(dds, contrast=c('condition', 'Z18_intron', 'eGFP_intron'))
dds_rrp40_intron <- results(dds, contrast=c('condition', 'RRP40_intron', 'EGFP_intron'))
plotMA(dds_ars_intron, ylim=c(-4,4), main='siARS2 vs siEGFP Refseq intron')

plotMA(dds_z18_intron, ylim=c(-4,4), main='siZ18 vs siEGFP Refseq intron')

plotMA(dds_rrp40_intron, ylim=c(-4,4), main='siRRP40 vs siEGFP Refseq intron')

Combine the results into on tidy data.frame

result_df <- function(deseq_result, title) {
  deseq_result %>%
  data.frame %>%
  rownames_to_column(var='id') %>%
  dplyr::select(id, log2FoldChange, padj) %>%
  mutate(main_run = title)
}


Refseq_introns_DESeq2_results <- result_df(dds_ars_intron, 'CI siARS2') %>%
  bind_rows(., result_df(dds_z18_intron, 'MA siZ18')) %>%
  bind_rows(., result_df(dds_rrp40_intron, 'MA siRRP40')) %>%
  mutate(main_run = factor(main_run, levels=c('CI siARS2', 'MA siZ18', 'MA siRRP40'))) %>%
  tbl_df
